<br>
On the other hand, I can understand it. The content is so very fucked up, its not the players' fault that the content was poorly implemented which allows these things to happen in the first place. It isn't the players' fault a large majority of guilds that kill Seru can get around even dodging the AE due to &quot;clever&quot; use of zone geometry. There does come a point when after so many VT clearings you just go &quot;fuck it, I just want to get this over with so I can go back to enjoying the game&quot; and people do make poor decisions like this for the sake of not wanting to make their gaming experience more of a hassle than it already is. Simple tip here as to what quantifies an exploit and what doesn't : odds are, anything which totally trivializes an encounter or places a mob where it should not be simply by logic standards is an exploit. Sorry but it is.<br>
<br>
I'm sorry the officers were suspended (I think a warning should have been issued well before this even occured before just jumping to suspension), I agree that really sucks, it pisses off a lot of people, and makes the game even less enjoyable than it has become, but you are as much at fault here as he is. I'm sure a big wad of flames will preceed this but eh, I'll say it as I see it.<br>
